      "writtenOn": "2026-03-26T15:12:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Jagpal pointed this out before, please let me know if further changes are needed after reviewing my response below.\n\nThe second arg is the string \"target\", which is used to identify the firmware slot\nAs we knew, there are two firmware slots, CFG0 and CFG1, in Lattice XO5 and XO3 CPLDs.\nHowever, Lattice XO5-15D is a special CPLD. It also has two firmware slots, but they are represented using image IDs: image 1 and image 2.\n\nWe do not assume that the active image is always image 1 or image 2. Instead, we send the “Check Current Running Image Status” command to the CPLD to determine the active image ID dynamically.\nTherefore, we keep the existing code framework, but do not use the string \"target\", and instead determine the active image ID at runtime.\n\nExample flow\nIf the active image ID is 2:\n1.Check current image status → active image ID \u003d 2\n2. Erase image ID 1\n3. Program image ID 1\n4. Perform a dry run on image ID 1\n5. Get dry-run result\n6. Set image ID 1 as the primary image for the next power cycle\n\nThis update flow is defined by Lattice and ensures CPLD firmware redundancy.",
      "parentUuid": "3526482b_3a137751",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "1b9fea4086540b8dbc9f1feb32363783490571a7",
